gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 117, Cavaliers 111
gameRecap.excerpt: Phoenix defeats Cleveland, 117-111. For Phoenix, the “Big 3” shined to lead the way with Kevin Durant (37 points (five 3PM), eight rebounds, six assists), Devin Booker (27 points, six rebounds, seven assists), and Bradley Beal (24 points, five rebounds, four assists, three steals) combining for 88 in the victory. Darius Garland finished with 30 points (seven 3PM) and five assists while Caris LeVert recorded 17 points, six rebounds, and 11 assists for Cleveland in the losing effort. Phoenix improves to 38-27, while Cleveland moves to 41-24 in the loss.
